RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOREVER FRIENDS reserved off the pace to the turn, circled four wide to commence his rally, engaged the pacesetter in deep stretch and pulled clear at the wire in a drive. CHA CHA LARRY sped up to set an early pressured pace, cleared into the turn, maintained his advantage to midway down the lane and was out-finished inside the final sixteenth while clearly second best. FOREVER LASTING tracked the leader from the rail to be prominent turning for home and finished evenly. BIG CITY HEAT stalked the pace from two wide into the turn, rallied to the head of the lane and weakened down the stretch. YOSHIDA'S IMPACT raced wide down the backstretch and into the turn and failed to mount a closing rally. WE MISS OTIS went one-paced failing to menace. TURBONATOR was never a threat. PRADO CITY was not a factor.

ENTRY.OWNER: Robey Alysia and Cook Brian K
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, cleared, outfinished, second best

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAS ORO prompted the pace to midway on the bend, responded when called upon nearing the quarter pole, engaged the pacesetter in upper stretch and drew off down the lane. PHILIP SNOW set the pace on a comfortable lead, dug-in turning for home, finished willingly but could not hold off the winner. PAIGE PERFECT tracked the leaders into the turn, was called upon early to rally in the turn, could not gain on the leaders but finished the best of the rest. GRAY MIKE unhurried early on and made a steady mild rally to hit the board. MOTION TO ADJOURN raced mid-pack on the outside down the backside, dropped to the rear of the pack in the turn and passed weakening rivals down the lane. ZEN JOURNEY trailed most of the way and never threatened. JACK D was well placed chasing the pace to the turn and came up empty. SNERDLEY broke a step slow, rushed up along the fence to midway on the turn, stopped coming home and was vanned off after passing the wire. He was later discovered to have bled.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RACCOON RODEO was brushed at the start, bid four wide at the three-eighths pole, vied three wide briefly in the stretch, drew off at the eighth pole and won under mild urging. MOPED MO was off awkwardly, dueled outside of a rival, went clear at the quarter pole, but couldn't last while dueling for the place. SPOKEN CODE was impeded at the start, trailed, then found his best stride late outside. OX TAP was unrushed, bid in the five path at the quarter pole, then faltered the stretch. RUSTY stalked the early pace in the four path, then faded in the stretch. BEYOND STOKED was brushed at the start, dueled inside, then gave way in the stretch.
